        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 PW/6–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Brazilian Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Macedo Soares</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-06">June 6,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have the honor to communicate to Your Excellency that the Brazilian Government,
                    having for some time considered the aggression <pb facs="0642" n="628" xml:id="pg_628"/> of Japan against the United States of America as though it
                    were directed against Brazil itself and desiring to cooperate for the final
                    victory of the United Nations and their allies, resolved by a Decree dated today
                    to declare the existence of a state of war with the above mentioned aggressor
                    power.</p>
                <p>I take this opportunity to renew to Your Excellency Brazil’s confidence in the
                    triumph over the common enemy.</p>
                <p>Cordial salutations.<note n="34" xml:id="d477fn34">For text of reply to this
                        telegram by the Acting Secretary of State and a statement issued by him on
                        June 6, see Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi> June 10,
                        1945, p. 1061.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">José Roberto de Macedo Soares</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
